review_blob: This stuff is bad.  My friend from Rochester gave me this as a joke, and thats exactly what it is.  Oh well, sounds like the price is pretty low.
Copper color.  Sort of some fruit undertones.  Could be hopped more.  Not what my friend made it out to be, but whats one more rating?
The only beer I would really keep coming back to at the Rock Bottom.  Dark brown with a good caramel nut flavor.  Sits on the palate well.
beer_name: Rock Bottom Denver Mollys Titanic Brown Ale

review_blob: Pretty average IPA.  Normal citrus undertones some honey.  Looked like an IPA, smelled like one, and tasted like one.  Nothing to go out of your way for.
Dark black with a brown head.  Sort of tasted a little like a barley wine because you could taste the alcohol.  Almost light-medium bodied.  Decent choice, but they have better.
Pretty average ale . Decent bittering hops, but the malt left a little to be desired.  Apparently this is their best seller, but I wouldnt waste my time with it again.
Dark brown with a tan head.  Great smokey malt with a medium body.  Sat on the palate well.  Best beer I had at the place.
Dark brown with an amber hue.  Some chocolate and roast aroma, but nothing overwhelming.  Good bittering hops, although I wouldnt mind seeing more aroma hops used.
Light red with a hint of amber.  Decent head.  Smells and tastes of cherries.  Other than that the flavor isnt too complex.  Decent palate but doesnt knock you off your feet.
Dark red with a froathy light tan head.  Solid hoppy aroma with a hint of some malt.  Tastes a lot like a pale ale, but has a mellow sweetness that comes out as you drink the beer.
Basically youre generic above average beer.  Not a ton of flavor but worth drinking
beer_name: Tap Room No. 21 Moes Backroom Amber Ale

review_blob: Dark brown with a light tan head.  Taste is full of roasted chocolate (sort of tastes like a less watered down version of the Total Eclipse Stout).  Sits on the palate nicely and reminds you that you had a great beer.  Easy to see why it is on the top 50 on rate beer at the moment
Dark black, little head.  Roasty flavor that sits on the palate nicely.  Nice and dry.  Worth a try.
beer_name: Wye Valley Dorothy Goodbodys Wholesome Stout

review_blob: Dark black with little head.  Very roasty, choclate taste.  Leaves a good impression on the palate.  Solid beer.

I had this one at the brewpub before watching my Wake Forest Demon Deacons beat the heels in football.

Golden amber color with a pretty citrus aroma. Good hoppy beer.  Not overzealous on the head like some IPAs, worth a try
beer_name: Top of the Hill Rams Head IPA

review_blob:
Got this at the brewpub before watching my Wake Forest Demon Deacons take it to the Heels in football.

Dark black with a typical nitrogen head.  Heavily roasty aroma and flavor with a hint of chocolate.  Pretty good
beer_name: Top of the Hill Frank Graham Oatmeal Porter

review_blob: Dark beer much like there stout.  Almost no head, but who cares.   Great coffee taste, and you can definitely pick up on the warmth from the 9%.  Its debatable which is better here the porter or the stout, but you cant go wrong here either way.
Dark brown with a froathy light brown head.  Pretty hoppy beer much like an IPA, but with more roasty undertones like a stout.  Still a lot of citrus.   Pretty good brew.
Pretty good beer.  Sort of bitter for a scottish ale.  More hoppy than most.  Still worth a try.
Dark brown with a light tan head.  Good lacing.  Nutty aroma with the flavor to back it up.  Sits well on the palate.  Good find for the airport bar
beer_name: Carolina Beer Co. Cottonwood Low Down  Brown Ale

beer_brewer_name: Old Dominion Brewing Company (Coastal Brewing Co.)
review_blob:
Dulles Airport Brew Pub on a 5 hour layover:

Dark black with a tan head.  Looked like it had some nitrous action to it.  Malty aroma with a good oak hint.  Creamy malty flavor with a little chocolate sprinkled in.  Also now that I think about it you can get a good bourbon hint to it.  The head is very good to swish around the mouth for awhile and it leaves a nice impression on your palate.  Definitely was a high point of my layover.
Looks like a beer, tastes better than most cheap beers and hell at 4.99 a 12 pack how can you go wrong.

A less putrid version of the classic Miller High Life.  Looks the same smells the same, but doesnt have quite the bite.  Still, do you want to pay yuengling prices for a special version of the High Life?
Pretty decent beer.  Reminds me a little of a german style brew, but definitely nothing overwhelmingly good.  Give it a shot.
Watery yellow with a small, white head.  Full bodied hoppy aroma.  Slightly piney floral flavor that makes a dry lasting impression on the palate.  Definitely worth a go.
Dark brown with an orange hue.  Nice froathy head.  Flavor is full of figs and other fruits.   Lingers nicely on the palate.  Good Brew
A little lighter in color than most imperial stouts.  Pretty roasty in flavor.  Good beer, but ive had better imperial stouts.
Dark brown with a small light tan head.   Good malty aroma with a taste to match.  Decent on the palate.
Clear yellow beer very little head.  Not a very overwhelming aroma and the taste leaves a lot to be desired.  Nothing is really wrong here, but nothing is really right either.
AMber with a good thick head.   Good aroma.  Good malty flavor that resinates in the mouth.  Suprisingly clean finish for a double bock.
Light bown with a nice froathy head.  Very nutty aroma.  Very warm tasting beer with a lot of malt.  Good fig taste.  Flavor lingers well and slowly dissapates.  Good brew.

Murkey brown with a nice froathy head.  Heavy fruit aroma fills the nostrils nicely (on a side note ive got a cold and the aroma feels good on my soar throat).  More alcoholic flavor than the other scotch ale that I had.  Still a pretty earthy flavor.   Palate lingers nicely.  Grab one.
Got this as a draught.  Hazy orange/brown color with little head.  Good citrus flavor and aroma.  Solid brew.  I hate how they serve this in a 12 ounce at Foothills instead of their usual pint.
ah not terrible.  Fortunately I didnt pay for it because a budweiser representative was at the local hams restaurant and gave me a free sample.  I do like free beer.
First of all im not a big fan of the style.  Decent citrus aroma.  Murky yellow color (its a hefeweizen).  Not much flavor to be honest and not much palate.  Just not a fan
Little head, dark brown.  Full body malt aroma.  Pretty good coffee flavor but seems watered down.  Rests decently on the palate.

Golden in color with a froathy head.  Traditional ale slightly woody aroma.  Void of much real flavor.  Finishes clean and does not make an impression on the palate.  Big dissapointment compared to Harpoons IPA offering.
Nice amber color.  Aroma is full of citrus.   Good citrus flavor that lingers nicely on the palate.  I am a mark of this beer
Deep amber with a small head.   Good malty aroma.   Full of caramen flavor and rests warmly on the palate.  Pretty good beer.
Dark black with a light tan head.  Good malty aroma.   Decent malty character but isnt very "full bodied"  doesnt really linger on the palate.

Flowery aroma.  Dark like dirty watter with a good sized head.   Slightly sweet with a malty floral character, very little hop action.      Doesnt really leave a lasting impression on the palate.  Worth a try at 2.50 a bottle

Dark amber in color with a big head.  Malty and fruity aroma.  Wheat and fruit are present in the flavor and the beer foams up in your mouth nicely as you swish it around.  Great lasting palate.  Great beer
Dark black with a light tan head.  Has a strong coffee aroma and taste delivers it.  Full body palate that fills the mouth for a good while.  Worth having.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Golden with a light head.  Citrus aroma.  Flavor is full of citrus and a slight bit of honey.  Sits nicely on the palate but nothing incredible.  Pretty good brew.
Yellow with a hint of amber with a thick white head.  Decent hop character in the aroma.  Sweet flavor with a very mild aftertaste.  Doesnt really overwhelm you, but not a bad beer.
Light yellow (lighter than most pale ales that I have had).  Aroma isnt very strong but favors the citrus.  Taste is full of citrus with a good bitter finish.  Decent option.

Light amber in color with a decent sized head.   Floral aroma almost like an IPA.  Woody character with a slight citrus hint.  Flavor lingers on the palate nicely as the bitterness dissapates off and leaves a spicy aftertaste.  Good brew.
This stuff is pretty bad.  Go with the Hurrican if your a hurting for a tall boy at the gas station.

Light yellow with next to no head.  Strong hint of corn with a little extra spice.  Flavor is full of corn malt, but much better than your usual miller brew.  Still if this is the best miller can do...

Mississippi must have red clay because this "mud" is a dark amber. Aroma suggests a very malty brew, but taste suprises with a decent hop character.  Nothing overwhelming here, but worth a shot if you are just grabbing a beer.
